I had a few random ideas about how BT could be improved/nerfed to be more satisfying to play against, whether or not is actually needs to be weakened for balance reasons.
I imagine both of these could be applied either independently or together.

1) Make the BT kill grant depend on the total ratio of wolves to non-wolves - for instance, the BT gets the extra kill exactly and only when non-wolves outnumber wolves more than 2:1. This makes BT more of an acceleration mechanic, where it might bring the wolves uncomfortably close to parity but will never be the thing that reaches it. It also means that BT can get their powers back (or even not manifest them until mid-game) if a bunch of wolves get killed early.

And/or 2) Instead of the BT granting the wolves extra democratic kills, the BT itself does the extra kills. This doesn't impact the number of wolf kills per night while the BT is active, but it does make the BT more vulnerable, as they will be ones in harm's way for a Huntsman or visit intel check, making it easier for the village to eliminate.

Of course, I do look forward to discussing this more fully at some point, looking at the statistics and game archives to see if things are actually problematic with the BT. I just wanted to provide some ideas for what could be in the game instead to supply the BT's role of extra kill power.

To be fair, this game would have been very different if the seer had come forward on day 3. Easy to say in hindsight, and I'm not sure if I'd have come forward on day 3 in his shoes, but it would have changed things big time.
